Focus Keyword" type="custom_field" group="Custom Fields" group_id="Custom_Fields-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8796"><source><![CDATA[Wer frühzeitig damit beginnt, sein Vermögen auf künftige Erben zu übertragen, kann größere Beträge steuerfrei weitergeben. Der persönliche Freibetrag ist dabei in den meisten Fällen gleich hoch. Bis zu diesem Betrag fällt für den Begünstigten keine Erbschaft- oder Schenkungsteuer an. Eine Ausnahme gibt es jedoch für Eltern und Großeltern: Ihr Freibetrag liegt bei der Erbschaftsteuer bei 100.000 Euro, während er bei der Schenkungsteuer nur 20.000 Euro beträgt. <em>„Grundsätzlich gilt: Je enger das verwandtschaftliche Verhältnis zwischen Erblasser oder Schenker und dem Empfänger ist, desto höher ist der Freibetrag</em>“ so Rechtsanwalt István Cocron.]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[Those who start transferring their assets to future heirs at an early stage can pass on larger amounts tax-free. In most cases, the personal allowance is the same. Up to this amount, the beneficiary is not liable for inheritance or gift tax. However, there is an exception for parents and grandparents: their allowance for inheritance tax is €100,000, while for gift tax it is only €20,000. "As a general rule, the closer the family relationship between the testator or donor and the recipient, the higher the allowance," says lawyer István Cocron.]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Heading (H2)" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8797"><source><![CDATA[<strong>Steuerklasse beeinflusst den Steuersatz</strong>]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[<strong>Tax bracket affects tax rate</strong>]]></target><note>wrap_tag:h2</note><tool:extradata unit="Heading (H2)" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8798"><source><![CDATA[Der Verwandtschaftsgrad entscheidet nicht nur über den Freibetrag, sondern auch über die Zuordnung zu einer Steuerklasse. Ehepartner oder Kinder des Verstorbenen zahlen geringere Steuersätze als entferntere Verwandte oder nicht verwandte Begünstigte. Steuerpflichtig wird nur der Teil des Nachlasses, der den persönlichen Freibetrag übersteigt. Die folgende Übersicht zeigt die Freibeträge und Steuerklassen entsprechend dem Verwandtschaftsgrad:]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[The degree of kinship determines not only the allowance, but also the tax bracket. Spouses or children of the deceased pay lower tax rates than more distant relatives or non-related beneficiaries. Only the portion of the estate that exceeds the personal allowance is taxable. The following overview shows the allowances and tax brackets according to the degree of kinship:]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8799"><source><![CDATA[<strong>Verwandtschaftsgrad</strong>​                                           <strong>Freibetrag</strong>]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[<strong>Degree of kinship</strong>                                           <strong>Exemption amount</strong>]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8800"><source><![CDATA[Ehepartner, Lebenspartner​                                           500.000 Euro]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[Spouse, life Partner                                           500,000 euros]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8801"><source><![CDATA[Kinder, Stiefkinder​                                                       400.000 Euro]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[Children, stepchildren: $400,000]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8802"><source><![CDATA[Enkelkinder​                                                                200.000 Euro]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[Grandchildren: $200,000]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8803"><source><![CDATA[Eltern, Großeltern​                                                       100.000 Euro]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[Parents, grandparents                                                       100,000 euros]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8804"><source><![CDATA[Geschwister, Nichten, Neffen, geschiedene Ehepartner​  20.000 Euro]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[Siblings, nieces, nephews, divorced spouses: €20,000]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8805"><source><![CDATA[Alle übrigen Erben​                                                       20.000 Euro]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[All other heirs: 20,000 euros]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Heading (H2)" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8806"><source><![CDATA[<strong>Steuersätze steigen mit der Höhe des Erbes</strong>]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[Tax rates increase with the size of the inheritance.]]></target><note>wrap_tag:h2</note><tool:extradata unit="Heading (H2)" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8807"><source><![CDATA[Neben der Steuerklasse spielt auch die Höhe des Nachlasses eine Rolle für den Steuersatz. Je höher das vererbte Vermögen, desto mehr Erbschaftsteuer fällt an. Die folgende Tabelle zeigt die Steuersätze nach Steuerklassen:]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[In addition to the tax bracket, the amount of the inheritance also plays a role in determining the tax rate. The higher the inherited assets, the more inheritance tax is payable. The following table shows the tax rates according to tax brackets:]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8808"><source><![CDATA[<strong>Vermögen</strong>​                     <strong>Klasse I</strong>​<strong>Klasse II</strong>​<strong>Klasse III</strong>]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[<strong>Assets</strong>​                     <strong>Class I</strong>​<strong>Class II</strong>​<strong>Class III</strong>]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8809"><source><![CDATA[Bis 75.000 Euro​                7 %​   15 %​30 %]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[Up to €75,000 7% 15% 30%]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8810"><source><![CDATA[Bis 300.000 Euro​              11 %​    20 %​30 %]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[Up to €300,000              11%              20%              30%]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8811"><source><![CDATA[Bis 600.000 Euro​              15 %​    25 %​30 %]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[Up to €600,000              15%    25%    30%]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8812"><source><![CDATA[Bis 6.000.000 Euro​              19 %​    30 %​30 %]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[Up to €6,000,000              19%              30%              30%]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8813"><source><![CDATA[Bis 13.000.000 Euro             ​    23 %​    35 %​50 %]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[Up to €13,000,000             ​    23%​    35%​50%]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8814"><source><![CDATA[Bis 26.000.000 Euro​               27 %​    40 %​50 %]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[Up to €26,000,000               27%    40%    50%]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8815"><source><![CDATA[Über 26.000.000 Euro​    30 %​    43 %​50 %]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[Over €26,000,000    30%    43%    50%]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Heading (H2)" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8816"><source><![CDATA[<strong>Freibeträge alle zehn Jahre nutzen</strong>]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[<strong>Take advantage of tax allowances every ten years</strong>]]></target><note>wrap_tag:h2</note><tool:extradata unit="Heading (H2)" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8817"><source><![CDATA[Ein großes Vermögen kann durch frühzeitige Schenkungen effektiv übertragen werden. Dabei lassen sich die Freibeträge bei der Schenkungsteuer alle zehn Jahre erneut ausschöpfen. Wer früh genug beginnt, kann hohe Summen steuerfrei weitergeben. Ein 60-Jähriger könnte beispielsweise bis zu seinem 80. Geburtstag jedem Kind 1,2 Millionen Euro schenken, für jedes Enkelkind kämen weitere 600.000 Euro hinzu.]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[A large fortune can be effectively transferred through early gifts. The gift tax allowances can be reused every ten years. Those who start early enough can pass on large sums tax-free. For example, a 60-year-old could gift each child €1.2 million by their 80th birthday, with an additional €600,000 for each grandchild.]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Heading (H2)" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8818"><source><![CDATA[<strong>Versorgungsfreibetrag nur bei Erbschaften</strong>]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[<strong>Maintenance allowance only for inheritances</strong>]]></target><note>wrap_tag:h2</note><tool:extradata unit="Heading (H2)" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8819"><source><![CDATA[Zusätzlich zu den Freibeträgen gibt es bei der Erbschaftsteuer für Ehepartner und Kinder bis 27 Jahre einen Versorgungsfreibetrag. Dieser liegt für Ehepartner und Lebenspartner bei 256.000 Euro. Für Kinder bis 5 Jahre beträgt er 52.000 Euro und sinkt mit steigendem Alter auf 10.300 Euro für junge Erwachsene zwischen 20 und 27 Jahren. „<em>Dieser Versorgungsfreibetrag kann nicht bei Schenkungen genutzt werden, sondern gilt nur bei Erbschaften</em>“ erklärt Rechtsanwalt Cocron.]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[In addition to the allowances, there is a maintenance allowance for spouses and children up to the age of 27 in relation to inheritance tax. This allowance is €256,000 for spouses and life partners. For children up to the age of 5, it is €52,000 and decreases with age to €10,300 for young adults between the ages of 20 and 27. "This maintenance allowance cannot be used for gifts, but only applies to inheritances," explains attorney Cocron.]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Heading (H2)" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8820"><source><![CDATA[<strong>Erbschaftsteuer für Immobilien</strong>]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[<strong>Inheritance tax on real estate</strong>]]></target><note>wrap_tag:h2</note><tool:extradata unit="Heading (H2)" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit><trans-unit resname="Paragraph" restype="string" datatype="html" id="package-string-151-8821"><source><![CDATA[Immobilien stellen oft einen Sonderfall bei der Erbschaft dar. Ehepartner und Kinder des Verstorbenen können eine selbst genutzte Immobilie steuerfrei erben, sofern sie eine Wohnfläche von maximal 200 Quadratmetern hat und mindestens zehn Jahre selbst genutzt wird. In diesen Fällen wird der Wert der Immobilie nicht auf die übrigen Freibeträge angerechnet. Für alle anderen Erben gilt: Der Verkehrswert der Immobilie wird auf die Erbschaft angerechnet, wobei lediglich der Freibetrag abgezogen wird. Da die Regelungen im Erbschaftsteuergesetz sehr detailliert sind, ist es ratsam, bei der Vererbung von Immobilien einen Steuerberater hinzuzuziehen.]]></source><target state="translated" state-qualifier="tm-suggestion"><![CDATA[Real estate often represents a special case in inheritance. Spouses and children of the deceased can inherit a property they have used themselves tax-free, provided that it has a living space of no more than 200 square meters and has been used by them for at least ten years. In these cases, the value of the property is not counted toward the remaining allowances. For all other heirs, the market value of the real estate is counted toward the inheritance, with only the allowance being deducted. Since the provisions of the Inheritance Tax Act are very detailed, it is advisable to consult a tax advisor when inheriting real estate.]]></target><tool:extradata unit="Paragraph" type="text" group="Main Content" group_id="Main_Content-0"/></trans-unit></body></file></xliff>